      "fullContent": "8.9 Million AI Users | Tomasz Tunguz Tomasz Tunguz Venture Capitalist at Theory Ventures\nIn short : Ollama makes open models effortless to run locally on a laptop or in the cloud with the same experience. 8.9m developers, 67,000 integrations, & partnerships with every major model lab & hardware vendor. Theory led the Series B.\nIt all started when I knocked on a door in Palo Alto.\nI noticed the little llama icon on the door & remembered how much I loved the product. Michael opened the door & welcomed me in. That is how I became friends with the Ollama founders, Jeff Morgan & Michael Chiang .\nSince then, I have migrated most of my workloads to Ollama ; it turns out I’m not alone.\nMore than 8.9m developers use Ollama, a number growing by nearly one million every week.\nThese users run Claude Code, Codex, OpenClaw, Hermes, & 65,000 more applications & integrations on top of Ollama.\nOllama makes AI simple. Download the app & start running AI on your laptop in seconds. Here it is running on my Macbook :\nI run open source models locally for 70-80% of my work & then burst to the Ollama cloud for complex tasks ; a cloud that is twice as fast as others.\n85% of the Fortune 500 uses Ollama across healthcare, finance, & energy. We found Ollama monitoring electricity loads at a powerplant in Finland ; at a space agency in the USA ; in the CFO’s office at a public company validating financials ; & even at a particle accelerator.\nData never leaves the user’s machine when running locally. Businesses can customize their AI & own it.\nOllama has partnered with every major open-source model provider including Google, Meta, NVIDIA, Microsoft, Zhipu, DeepSeek. Ollama offers thousands of models like GLM-5.2, Kimi K2.7, Gemma, Qwen, & Ornith .\nToday we announced our investment leading Ollama’s $65m Series B, alongside Benchmark, YC, & others.\nThe future of AI is open models running everywhere work gets done. Jeff & Michael built Docker’s developer experience. Now they’re building it for AI.\nIf you want to run an open model, start here .\nGet the next one in your inbox\nThe 1-minute read that turns tech data into strategic advantage. Read by 150k+ founders & operators.\nRelated Posts\nLocalmaxxing\nMAY 11, 2026 Full Sail on Asynchronous Inference\nJUNE 25, 2026 So You Want to Sell Inference\nJUNE 22, 2026\nGP at Theory Ventures. Former Google PM. Sharing data-driven insights on AI, web3, & venture capital.\nBloomberg • WSJ • Economist"
